<Date>1594328237400</Date><username>Cyn Thompson< /username><rating>3< /rating><pictures>None<//pictures>< resp>
None< /resp>
<gmap_id>0x80e830bccd7de641:0xafcda73403f35038< /gmap_id><UserId.>118049527235161339920</UserId.>< Review>
The really enjoy eating at Panda Express. They're a little more on the expensive side in terms of fast food restaurants so it's kind of a special treat when I do go there for my family. My problem is with the soy sauce. I happen to really enjoy my Chinese food a lot more when I have soy sauce with it. For some reason at Panda Express they make you ask for the soy sauce when you at the register when you pay for your order. That is fine. But when the cashier acts as though they are going way out of their way to get you some or simply lies to you completely about putting some in your bag already, that's what irks me. That's exactly what happened to me three nights ago. I didn't realize until I got home, a few miles away from the store that the cashier lied to my face and put no soy sauce packets in my bag. They act like the cost for those packets come out of their daily wages or something. I realize I can go to the grocery store and buy some for myself which is what I'll do, but my point is that's something they provide with your meal there and why should I be made to feel like I'm bothering the staff for asking for some or just flat out be lied to? I know I'm not the only person who feels this way about Panda Express, I've spoken to many people who all feel the same way. I wonder how many  customers they've lost over this.< /Review>

< text>
The restaurant was clean, and it was cool on a hot day. We enjoyed the Mexican music, and the chips and salsa were really good. We thought the prices were high, so we ordered a la carte - but still paid more than we wanted. I had a chicken mol√© enchilada, which was okay. I've enjoyed it much more elsewhere, but I'm assuming that's just personal preference. I also had a chicken taco, which I really enjoyed. I don't remember what my husband ate, but I do know he got the horchata and after tasting it I was really jealous. So good, and freshly made!< /text>

Excellent authentic Mexican food!  One of my top 3 favorites.  Extensive menu and reasonably priced.  I love their Quesadillas!  They stuff them with chicken or carnitas, or just cheese. < text>
Red curry had a really nice classic flavor to it with a thick creamy coconut milk base and a Thai basil touch. Chicken skewers (satay) were also really juicy and solid with the various condiments they have out. My girlfriend dropped a chicken skewer and they whipped up a whole new order for her. Super nice guys, solid customer service, great curry paste flavor.</text>

< Review>
A gem of a place! Glad our friends introduced us to this restaurant. The spice level ranges from 1-5 on the menu.  Everything ordered this evening was delicious, including: the pad see ewe, drunken noodles, Tom Ka, and fried rice.

The Thai iced tea was sweet with just enough cream to balance out the flavor.<//Review>

< text>
I found E Patisseria this AM and I will say, WOW! (as I did several times when I was there).

I like everything about this new Cafe (6 months old). I met the gracious owner Elizabeth who shares with me that she is the designer also. The cafe is gorgeous, two artful rooms with plenty of seating to accommodate various sizes groups. They also have a nice patio in the back with additional seating at the front of the Cafe (which is Main St the old gentrified section of Garden Grove).

The servers where very nice (I recommended a raise for both of them).

They have an open kitchen (very clean and we'll organized). Plenty of Patisserie choices.

E Patisserie also offers some interesting products and they have a bridal boutique to the back of the larger dining area.

The Village area of Garden Grove is also very nice with plenty of shopping within a short walk from E Patisserie.

You will enjoy your time in this feel good, feel very good Cafe de excellente!!!

cmilton111
Google Guide
2.16.2018<//text>

<Text>The delight of Garden Grove!  This place is the epitomy of a friendly downtown merchant, and is such a great addition to the old downtown Garden Grove.  My family has met the pastry chef owner, her mom, and their amazing pastry chef, Roger.  They are good people. The two chefs met in training under a world-renowned French pastry chef, and El Patisserie was born.
Their shop is a cozy, clean & modern oasis in the old town district. The environment is fresh and beautiful, made such by their gorgeous and equally delicious pastries.  Their is seating inside, out front, and on the quaint back patio.  Free wifi too!  The staff is very friendly and are willing to please.  These guys are out to make their mark on Main Street.

Try their coffee, it's delicious! I'm also a huge fan of their yummy sweet almond croissants.  They are buttery deliciousness topped with roasted sliced almonds and almond paste inside or on the bottom. Pair this with the coffee and you have a winner!  Try their quiche too.  I like the sausage variety.  I think they have different flavors on different days too.   This place uses nothing but the finest ingredients and real butter.  Get yours before this place is discovered and they run out of food by 10 with huge lines of people out the front door.  That's what I predict for these guys. They are doing it right and that will not go unnoticed.<//Text>< name>
Sierra Nets</name>

<review>Here's a gem in Garden Grove.  Cute little French pastries and light lunches served.  The prices are reasonable and the pastries are excellent.  The panini was good but I really loved the crab quiche.  Light and refreshing, not like the usual quiche Lorraine or spinach.   The quiche is exactly like it is made in France, the filling light and the crust perfectly cooked.  The croissant was excellent. Really!!  Finally after three years I have found my perfect croissant like I used to eat in France and Switzerland.  OMG, I was in heaven.  The canel√© was pretty good, the interior was perfect, the extra needed to be a little more crispy but it was still good.  Believe me, even in France some places can't make them the way they should be.  The only guy I know is one from Bordeaux and he's been making them for forty years....  I do want to say that the owners should watch out...some other French patesserie or five star hotel just might come along and steal their pastry chef... < rate>
3<//rate>
< Review>
Ordering online for pickup at 6:30 on a Saturday is a mistake.  Instead of selecting ASAP, I selected a time a little later. Got there on time and had to wait outside for 20 minutes. They have you write your name on a board with a clean pen and wait outside. People were coming and going that ordered inside.  I will not go at that hour again. Too many people for a small space inside and a small area to wait outside. Clearly, they are doing something right, since soooo many people go there. My experience picking up much later or on an off hour works far more smoothly.  Presently, they have a deal online, that if you buy a $30 gift card, you get a free bowl ($6.80 before tax). Also, if you fill out survey (see your receipt) within 2 days, you can get a free entree item on next order with the purchase of a 2 entree plate. Their fried rice was great. We also like the veggie spring rolls. I WISH they would bring back their hot & sour soup.< /Review>

I told her my former doctor was Dr. Zingaro and I was pleased to hear he is still there after all these years.

I understand that everyone has their opinion, but it seems like it's only when people are upset that they go online and talk about it. If as many people took the time to share their wonderful experiences, I think you would find a far more balanced rating. That goes with any business. I am a business owner and shudder to think how badly affected my business would be if one negative interaction was posted when I have so many wonderful, devoted clients.

I guess ultimately it is incumbent upon us to do our own research and make choices for ourselves rather than immediately believe negativity.

I love Sono Bello and look forward to my next experience with them.</review><Pics>None<//Pics>< Resp>

< Review>
The customer service was great. My doctor did the procedure well. I'm happy with the results. I just wouldn't recommend this place if you're someone who's even a little bit resistant to Lidocaine. It turned out Lidocaine doesn't work on me...at all. And they don't have a general anesthesia option. So once we got started I was stuck until we finished. They didn't force me to continue. I chose to tough it out rather than end up with a lopsided area, but I can't tell you how brutal the pain was. The whole thing is pretty medieval when you can feel all of it.

The doctor did what he could do as quickly and carefully as possible. They kept a close eye on my vital signs in case I passed out from the pain. They were very kind and concerned for my well being. They finished my hips and belly, and the procedures they weren't able to complete were refunded to my credit card. I don't blame anyone at Sono Bello for what I went through. None of us knew this was going to happen. And they absolutely tried to make it right.

If they eventually offer general anesthesia I'd gladly go there again. In the meantime, I'm hesitant to recommend them.
If this helps at all: I've looked into it and some studies show that resistance to Lidocaine is often genetic. It's more common in redheads and can run in families of Irish descent. I'm not a scientist, but if you fall in either of those categories you might want to ask around in your family and see if anyone else has a resistance to Lidocaine. I found out after the fact that it runs in my family.<//Review>

This review is in reference to Howe Avenue location in Sacramento, CA. First off, I scheduled an appointment for a "free consultation" prompted by a radio ad that stated, "Receive $500.00 off if you schedule your appointment BY December 31, 2017." Semantics is important and ADVERTISING is tricky. I called to be sure that "BY" didn't mean get $500.00 off if you schedule to have the service performed BEFORE December 31 OR it if meant that as long as I scheduled the appointment for ANY date before or AFTER December 31, I would receive the discount. The person who answered didn't know for sure and had someone call me who stated that as long as I paid $1,000.00 down, I would receive the discount! Even though I thought that was pretty f'd up (and FALSE ADVERTISING), I wanted to have some things done, so I went to the scheduled appointment. I arrived at 10:37a for my 10:30 appointment. There were a couple of people leaving and one person waiting. I was given paper work to complete, which took about ten minutes. Several more people with appointments arrived after me. After about 30 minutes, the lady who had been waiting before I arrived, was called in. It was apparent that she was actually having a procedure, not a consultation (she'd brought a change of clothes, and her husband, who'd accompanied her, was told where he could wait.) Thirty minutes later (a full hour at that point) I was still waiting. I asked the receptionist how much longer it would be. She stated that the doctor was 45 minutes behind schedule! Apparently, there was NO ONE ELSE to do consultations! I didn't have a problem with the actual doctor doing the consult (better, IMO), but I DID have a problem with her expecting me to wait until she could fit me in! This ish isn't cheap and MY time is just as valuable as hers! I will go to an office that RESPECTS that.</Text>

< Review>
I would recommend Sono Bello to anyone who needed to finally be happy in their own skin. It has been 20 years of battling with my weight. I lost 122 pounds with Jenny Craig way back in the 90's. Then as most people do I kept it off until I had kids. I have maintained my wieght pretty well over th last 10 years, but I have twins and 2 other children. My body wasn't responding to all the running and excercising I have been doing daily. My mid-section and inner thighs didn't look like I am running a 10min mile. I just needed to be happy again.I am still not back up to running that 10 min mile yet. I am only 2 months into my recovery. I am happy with the results so far. My pain level was like having a c-section in my abdomin and my inner thighs were swollen for about 2-3 weeks. Now, I would do it all over again. My "soccer" moms are noticing that my stomach is flatter and my clothes are fitting alot better. No more muffin top here. I can't wait to see the final results in a few more months. The staff at Sono Bello treated me great. They made me feel like all my concerns were legitimate and worth my concern. I was put at ease the minute I met Dr. Pardington. They are the best at what they do.< /Review>

< Review>
Obviously, as a GrubHub driver, I am privy to and receive a certain amount of respect and kindness shown to me by all restaurant employees. After all, we are colleagues and friends.

As for Red Robin in Roseville, California, I can tell you that a young lady named Kayla has shown me and our GrubHub customers a great deal of respect and kindness and assertiveness in making sure that each order is prepared correctly.

Believe me when I tell you that that is not where the service stops. Kindness and the art of loving and inclusiveness Has No Limitation.

So if you want to enjoy one America‚Äôs best burgers prepared in one of America‚Äôs best restaurants and served to you by one of the best servers in Roseville, California, go to Red Robin.

Ask for Kayla.

And let her present you with not just the best and most enjoyable night out, But one of the most heartfelt evenings you have ever experienced in your life.

I have to wonder how I could possibly be the kind of person that could know these beautiful human beings and call them friends.

< text>
If you have food allergies this is the place to go for a really good restaurant burger. Their web site has a allergen menu where you check off what you cant eat and they give you options on what's on the menu you can have. Also shows ways you can have menu items by removing what your allergic to. I had the big taco tavern burger on a gluten free bun with no cheese or sliced peppers with a side salad. I usually get the steamed broccoli which is also bottomless. Love coming here, we've always had great service from the wait staff.</text>

<Rating>1<//Rating>< review>
Red Robin is a titan that has fallen far from where it stood. I remember 10 plus years ago when going to Red Robin filled my young heart with excitement, however, not it seems like an empty husk of its former self. The food is mediocre at best, with their menu seemingly being downsized from what it used to be. The staff seem inconvenienced to take your order, let alone bring your drinks in a timely manner. After being asked about our appetizer that we order 15 minutes prior, we were told that it would come out with our entrees, which I dont need to explain the fault of this thinking process. After our meal showed up, the last time we saw our server is when she brought the check. This is a classic case of "Dont meet your childhood heroes". Unfortunately I would recommend to avoid this chain with a 10 foot pole, far from what it used to be.</review>

Not only was our food cold when it came out to us, it took an hour to get our orders and our drinks were never refilled. My husband had ordered a hamburger and got hardly any fries with it. I was 5 months pregnant at the time and I got very sick, my two year old son got very ill, and so did my husband. Needless to say we have no intention of every returning to this restaraunt. I've been to several different Red Robin's and have never been very impressed with the food anyway.< /Review>

<user_id>118236926311743032912</user_id><user_name>vl Reclee<//user_name><Date>1444799645068< /Date><rate>3</rate>< review>
Ordered your onion rings for take out. The gal in the bar who helped was very nice. Gave me what I asked for. 4 pkgs. knife,fork,spoons./w salt & pepper. I wanted salt. I needed the salt. Got my order to the car. I was starving so had a ring. Oh my god. They looked alittle to dark but I was in the car & it was night. But when I took a bite, I thought my teeth would start breaking. They where so 'crunchy' , hard!. And yes , they where very dark. I remember the rings there golden brown /w a soft crunch & tender onion inside.not so done that you could'nt see it! Needless to say I went home & finished the 13 rings. ALOT of the crunch in the bottom of the box /w a small pool of grease. They where still warm to the very last one. How do they do that & still keep the crunch?  Anyway, I will give them another try some day, inside.. with a burger. I'll ask for medium oinon rings.<//review>
